    "Otherwise, society must carry the burden of blackbox failures.",
    "All model decisions are rooted in the training data.",
    "Training data influence analysis [also known as data valuation (Ghorbani & Zou, 2019; Jia et al., 2019a; Ki et al., 2023) and data attribution (Park et al., 2023; Nguyen et al., 2023; Dai & Gifford, 2023) ] partially demystifies the relationship between training data and model predictions by determining how to apportion credit (and blame) for specific model behavior to the training instances (Shapley and Roth, 1988; Koh & Liang, 2017; Yeh et al., 2018; Pruthi et al., 2020).",
    "Essentially, influence analysis's objective is to answer the question: What is each training instance's effect on a model?",
    "An instance's \"effect\" is with respect to some specific perspective."
  ],
